          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_NYPA_EncoreBilling",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve billing information from a set of related tables within a SQL Server database. It focuses on billing periods for accounts associated with the New York Power Authority (NYPA) and involves calculations related to billing periods, payments, and account details. The procedure filters records based on a specified range of billing periods, using a custom function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CalculatePreviousBillingPeriod",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " to determine the relevant periods."
        }
      ]
    },
